# Android Builds From WSL

This repository is often worked on from WSL, but the Android IDE and SDK setup live in the Windows/JetBrains environment.

For any Android or mobile-project build, test, lint, or Gradle validation command, you MUST use the JetBrains MCP terminal tool from the IDE context instead of running the command in the WSL shell.

Use JetBrains MCP tools such as:
- `execute_terminal_command` for Gradle commands run from the IDE terminal
- `build_project` when an IDE build is the better fit

Do not run Android/KMM Gradle builds directly from the WSL shell unless the user explicitly asks for that fallback.

Reason: WSL shell runs do not have the correct mobile project environment in this setup and commonly fail, while JetBrains MCP executes against the actual IDE project context.
